      <br>
      <div class="container">
        <h3 style="text-align: left;">Circulation</h3>
        <p style="text-align: left;">Sometimes we may come across coverage from search/news portals which normally have very high circulation rates.</p>
        <hr>
        <br>
        <div class="key_elements">
          <ol><p class="primary-list-title">Starting FY22, we will adopt the below formula to get a more accurate and realistic read on the circulation:</p>

            <li class="secondary-list-title">All media platforms should fall under one of the below three categories.</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Category 1 - For mega national and global news portals: Main page monthly visits * news pageviews% * 10%</li>
              <li>Category 2a - For mainstream news sites, adopt the circulation numbers provided by the publications or available in their websites/latest media kits</li>
              <li>Category 2b - If numbers are not available from the publication itself: Main page monthly visits * news pageviews%</li>
              <li>Category 3 - Others: For sites that numbers are not available from the publication itself or have no pageviews% on hypestat.com, direct monthly visits # will be used</li>
            </ul>

            <li class="secondary-list-title">Coverage tonality/sentiment</li>
              <ul>
                <li>Tonality is categorized as positive, neutral and negative</li>
                <li>For <b>ALL COVERAGE TYPES EXCEPT</b> “Online - Reposting (exclude press release)”, they will be counted as <b>POSITIVE</b></li>
                <li>For <b>ALL “Online - Reposting (exclude press release)”</b> coverage, they will be counted as <b>NEUTRAL</b></li>
                <li>If a coverage is explicitly negative but falls under one of the categories from Row 11, then it will be counted as <b>NEGATIVE</b>.</li>
                <li>Objective industry analysis of Lenzing and product brands will be defined as neutral, unless explicit positive or negative wordings are used</li>
              </ul>

              <ol class="third-tier-list"><p class="secondary-list-details"><u>Remarks:</u></p>
                <li>All figures should be taken from Hypestat.com</li>
                <li>For Category 1, 10% is an estimation of the viewership of a B2B or industry specific news in the site.</li>
                <li>For streaming sites e.g. YouTube/ Youku which do have a news page unlike Yahoo, Sina etc. will also means there wont be a news% available on Hypestat - they will be considered as Category 3 media.</li>
                <li>Below shows some of the updated circulation numbers (as of Mar 2022) for the team's easier reference.</li>
              </ol>      
        </div>

